FBIS3-49581 "dreeu008_r_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 ROMANIA PUNR's Brahas To Head BUN Alliance AU1101195194 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 6 Jan 94 p 4 AU1101195194 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI Language: Romanian Article Type:BFN [Article by Crina Nedelcu: "The President of the National Unity Bloc Is Cornel Brahas, Deputy of the Romanian National Unity Party"] [Text] "In the first meeting of the National Unity Bloc [BUN] after its creation, both sides of the alliance [the Romanian National Unity Party (PUNR) and the Agrarian Democratic Party of Romania (PDAR)] agreed that this body should be led in the next six months by the PUNR," PDAR President Mr. Victor Surdu said. "At the same meeting, we elected the BUN leadership: Cornel Brahas, PUNR, becomes the executive president and Constantin Carbunaru, PDAR, the vice president," he added. Yesterday afternoon, a meeting was held at the PUNR headquarters in the Chamber of Deputies on the way in which PUNR will participate in the negotiations with the Social Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR] on the future form of government. "Until now," Mr. Victor Surdu said, "PUNR had a mandate from us to negotiate with the PDSR on behalf of PDAR, too. At the next meeting with the ruling party, BUN will be present, that is the PDAR representatives, too."
